{
  "texts": [
    "For example, we cannot defend against zero-day exploits on SROS, ROS2, the normal world kernel, or any of the components of Pd-Ros.",
    "We also assume that SROS completely mediates application communication within the normal world.",
    "A malicious ROS2 application can attempt to bypass SROS by directly invoking OS abstractions, e.g., via raw sockets, to communicate with a colluding application [16].",
    "Prior work has attempted to harden the normal world kernel against zero-day exploits [14,50], and to ensure that applications only communicate under the purview of SROS [9,16].",
    "Those methods also apply to our setting."
  ]
}